transcription.text:
Speaker 1: This is Jimmy.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Jimmy, my name's Antonio Wilkins, W-I-L-K-I-N-S, my address 2835 Barone Street, B-A-R-O-N-N-E,

Speaker 2: in New Orleans, Louisiana, 70115.

Speaker 1: All right, I got you up here, Mr. Wilkins, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Antonio Wilkins, yes, I ordered the, and I received the 40, the quantity of 40.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh.

Speaker 2: But what I ordered was the AGV, and I did not receive the AGV.

Speaker 1: I ordered 100 milligrams AGV.

Speaker 2: I called last Monday, and they told me they was going to resend it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And they haven't as of yet.

Speaker 1: So if it was sent, I need to know when it was going to be received or when it was going to be shipped.

Speaker 2: I never got any follow-up information on that.

Speaker 1: All right, let me check it out and see what's going on.

Speaker 2: But I did call about this a Monday ago, last week Monday.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh.

Speaker 2: Well, I see that it should be on the way to you, Antonio.

Speaker 1: So the schedule is due in about five days, so it is on the way.

Speaker 2: Five days from last Monday?

Speaker 1: Well, I'm looking at it because what the holdup was,

Speaker 2: because they didn't realize it was a replacement order,

Speaker 1: and it would have been too soon to send out another order.

Speaker 2: So one of the reps had to reach out to them and tell them that this is a replacement order.

Speaker 1: So that's what's going on on that.

Speaker 2: You understand what I mean?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: But is there any tracking number or something I can or do I just hang up and just cross my fingers to when it's going to come?

Speaker 1: No, no, it's going to come.

Speaker 2: I can see that there's going to be a tracking number available tomorrow to see the exact date.

Speaker 1: So if you want to give us a call back tomorrow, and I'm not trying to just tell you that,

Speaker 2: but it's going to be an exact date to show when it's going to arrive.

Speaker 1: Because I see that it's being handled with the post office right now,

Speaker 2: so they haven't had a tracking number assigned to it as of yet.

Speaker 1: So once the post office gets that tracking number.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I've got to call back again.

Speaker 1: Well, I'm just telling the situation account what the delay was,

Speaker 2: because they didn't realize it was a replacement order.

Speaker 1: They thought it was a reorder, and that's why it wasn't sent out immediately.

Speaker 2: Okay, so.

Speaker 1: But it's going to go out.

Speaker 2: It's going to go out.

Speaker 1: It's definitely been sent out to you.

Speaker 2: That's for sure.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: So I just want to confirm.

Speaker 1: This should be the ATP.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: The 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: And the 40 count.

Speaker 2: Well, that's what I'm looking at.

Speaker 1: I'm making sure that I'm going to make sure you get the 40 count too as well.

Speaker 2: That's what I'm saying, because it looks like they just reordered the standard of 25,

Speaker 1: and that's what I'm going to get involved now and make sure it's the 40 count.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's not what I ordered.

Speaker 1: I ordered the 40 count.

Speaker 2: And that's what I paid for.

Speaker 1: I see that was your first order.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: That's what I'm going to get involved.

Speaker 2: So I'm kind of glad that it was a delay,

Speaker 1: and make sure you get that extra 15 to go with the 25.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So we'll take care of that for you.

Speaker 2: I'll take care of that for you, actually.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Will they just upgrade that?

Speaker 1: Will I see that in my email or what?

Speaker 2: Because I don't want to just have to continuously call.

Speaker 1: No, no.

Speaker 2: And you know what?

Speaker 1: I'm going to expedite your delivery for you, too,

Speaker 2: for you to get it faster as I get it for you.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: So you're taken care of.

Speaker 1: If you don't get it by the end of today, it's Tuesday,

Speaker 2: if you don't get it by the end of this week, give us a call.

Speaker 1: My name is Jimmy, and I'm going to try to make sure you get an ASAP.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Goodbye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
